betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lThe Tool Forge is required to make higher tier tools like the Hammer.

§rMake a cast by pouring 2 ingots of either Gold or Alluminum Brass on a disposable Stone part of the Cast you want to make. To pour the material on a part, right click the part on the Casting Table and then activate the Faucet.

The Tool Forge can replace your Tool Station. It allows you to make additional, cooler tools like the Hammer or the Scythe. Some of the new tools require metal parts.
So, now that we have Steel, we can finally progress into the Steel Age.

§lThe IC2 path of getting Refined Iron, which also works as Steel, is a bit more involved. You need a ton of machines and infrastructure set up, but is faster once it's ready.

§rFirst, you need the Compressor. Put Empty Cells into it to make Compressed Air Cells.

The Blast Furnace does not use EU /or/ RF. It uses heat, which we will get using the Electric Heat Generator. EU comes into the Heat Generator from any side, except for the orange one, which is where heat comes out of. You need to have Coils in the Heat Generator as well. 2EU = 1hU. You cannot power the Electric Heat Generator directly through IE Wire Coils, you have to go through a BatBox (or any other IC2 storage) first.

The orange side of the Blast Furnace accepts heat, so you should put it up against the Heat Generator. Place the Compressed Air into the bottom left slot, and put Iron ingots into the slot above it. It will start to heat up, and once heat is at 100%, then it will start converting the Iron and Compressed Air into Refined Iron and Slag.

§lThaumcraft: Where even the most logical man becomes a gibbering mess, and loves every second of it.

§rAfter mining a Crystal and getting some rest, craft Salis Mundus and rightclick a bookshelf with it to get the Thaumonomicon, Thaumcraft's Guide Book.
§lThe Lexica Botania, while innacurate in recipes, explains how Botania's mechanics work.

§lThe Alloy Smelter is one of the easiest ways to make alloys, like Signalum. These alloys are required for some of the more advanced machines. You can put a Double-Layer or Octadic Capacitor in it to make it faster and hold more RF.

§rAn Alloy Smelter has 3 modes: Alloys only, Furnace only, and All Smelting.

§lThe Rock Crusher is a multiblock that uses RF to crush blocks. The crushed blocks are used in some recipes. You can also crush ores in this.

§rThe Rock Crusher is a 3x2x2 multiblock. Two rows of 3, with another layer exactly the same on top.

§lThe SAG Mill uses RF to crush ores and other blocks and items. In addition to a 100% chance to double ores, it has a small chance to give you dusts for other ores, and cobblestone.

§rYou can put Flint into the SAG Mill to multiply the main output by 1.2, bonus output by 1.25, and reduce power use by 15%. Later, you can put in Dark Steel Balls to multiply main output by 1.5, bonus output by 2, and reduce power use by 30%.

§lAn Ender Chest / Ender Pouch combo is great for moving items from your inventory back to your base. For instance, while Mining, you can put Ores into the Pouch, and then have the Ores sucked out of the Ender Chest into your storage or processing.

§rYou can right-click a diamond onto the chest jewel thing that pops out of the front to set it to your player. That way, a diamond white-white-white is different than the regular white-white-white. Shift-right-click the Ender Chest with the Ender Pouch to link to two.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Lava Comes In, Lava Comes Out
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lEnder Tanks work similar to Ender Chests, but for fluids. They are color coded by right-clicking the 3 wool bits at the top, and can be set to be specifically for your player by right-clicking the center bit with a diamond. Multiple tanks with the exact same color coordination and diamond share the same fluid inventory, so you can put one at, say, a lava pump in the Nether and put another next to your Smeltery to give your Smeltery essentially infinite lava.

§rRight click on the center-front bit to change it from input to automatically output below it, or to switch back to input.

§lTo run, it needs any Axe and Shears in the slots at the top. You can shift-click items into the Slice 'N' Splice and it will put the items where they need to go.

§rA task where the player needs specific items. These do not have to be handed in, having them in one's inventory is enough.

§lThe Soul Binder is used to Bind the Soul of mobs to items to create new items, usually used in crafting.

§rThe Soul Binder uses filled Soul Vials plus an item. To fill the Soul Vial, right click a mob with an empty Vial. Different recipes need different Souls.

§lThe Slaughterhouse uses RF to kill mobs in a 5x5x3 area in front of it. They do not drop anything, and instead, the Slaughterhouse gets some Meat, and rarely Pink Slime. The Precision Sledgehammer lets you see the area covered by MFR machines.

§rPink Slime is very useful for crafting, and makes for some pretty good Tinkers' tools. It would be best to automate the Mob Slaughter Factory with a mob farm or something similar.

§lThe Vat is where you make certain fluids, like Nutrient Distillation or Rocket Fuel. Pipe the input fluid into it, give it the correct ingredients, and then pipe out the resultant fluid.

§rRecipes can use several different ingredients in place of eachother, but they give different amounts of fluid.

§lThe Inscriber is used to make AE2 Processors, which are used in recipes. It requires RF to run.

§rThe Meteorite Compass points in the direction of the nearest AE2 meteorite. In the center of AE2 meteorites is a Sky Stone Chest that can have one of the Inscriber Presses.

In order to automate the Inscribers without having to move around the Presses, you need 5 Inscribers: 4 for the Inscriber Presses and 1 for making them into Processors. A good method of automating Inscribers is using Steve's Factory Manager.

You can make extra Presses of ones you have by putting it and an Iron Block in the Inscriber.

§lThe Petal Apothecary is how most Botanical flowers are created.

§rThe Petal Apothecary works same as allways, give it water and put the correct ingredients in, and then throw in Seeds. Interesting thing that many don't know, you can shift right click it with an empty hand while it's filled with water and you automatically put in the ingredients from the last thing you made.

§lThe Tunnel Bore is a special machine. It acts like a Minecart, in that it needs to be on tracks. Put Gravel into the Ballast slots, and it will place the Gravel if it ever comes accross a hole that it would usually fall into. Put Tracks into the Track slots so that it can place them in front of it and keep going. The Bore Head tiers are Iron < Steel < Diamond. Diamond is the only one that can mine Obsidian, and will dig a 700 block long tunnel.

§rAny fuel that would work in a furnace will work in the Fuel slots. Coal Coke is the best for this reason.

By default, the Tunnel Bore will just spit out the blocks mined into the world behind it. If you place a Chest Cart behind it and shift right click the Chest Cart and the Tunnel Bore with any Railcraft Crowbar, they will be linked. Once linked, items are pushed into that chest instead. You can do this with many chests to extend the inventory space.

§lThe RFTools Matter Transmitter and Matter Receiver are one of the easiest ways to go about teleporting.

§r§rThese both require RF to run, and don't passively use any. You should definitely name these, and set them to private if you don't want people to be able to teleport into your base.

The Dialing Device needs RF and needs to be nearby to a Matter Transmitter. The Dialing Device allows you to decide which Transmitter to send from, and which Reciever to send to. Basically, set where you are and where you want to go. This is why it's best to name the Matter Transmitter and Matter Receiver.

§lThe Compacting Drawer stores a block in 3 forms. For instance, if you put a Gold Ingot in it, you can pull out ingots, nuggets, or blocks, depending on how much you have. You can also use it to store Cobblestone, and it keeps it as regular Cobblestone, Compressed Cobblestone, and Double Compressed Cobblestone.

§rThe Compacting Drawer's maximum storage is based on the highest denomination. That is, it can hold 16 stacks of Iron Blocks, for instance.

§lWater Wheels generate RF based on the amount of flowing water blocks are touching it. All the water blocks have to be flowing with the wheel. You can have up to 3 Water Wheels per Kinetic Dynamo.

§rPlace down the Kinetic Dynamo and then place the Water Wheel on the side that looks like a copper coil. RF can be piped out from any side.

§lSome more of the mechanics added by Botania, mainly storing, moving, and using Mana.

§rThe Pure Daisy turns Stone into Livingrock and logs into Livingwood. These are very useful for crafting, and look quite nice for building. You can automate it using SFM's Block Gates or AE2's Formation and Annihilation Planes, among other things.

Mana Spreaders are how you move Mana. Put it down, shift right click a Wand of the Forest in Bind Mode first on the Mana Spreader and then on the Mana Pool. Mana generating flowers bound to the Mana Spreader put the Mana in there, and then the Mana Spreader puts it into the Mana Pool, or whatever else it's pointed at.

The Mana Pool is arguably the most important thing made by Livingrock. It is used to store Mana, which many things from Botania use as energy. You can craft things with it by throwing the ingredient in.

The Runic Altar is another of the crafting mechanics Botania offers. It requires you point a Mana Spreader at it, and then you throw all the ingredients onto it. Once it's done filling up with Mana, throw a Livingrock on it and right click it with a Wand of the Forest.

§lThe Improved Blast Furnace is basically the same as the regular Blast Furnace, except you can automate it and speed it up.

§rThe Improved Blast Furnace is a 3x3x3 of Reinforced Blast Bricks with a Hopper on top. Right-click the center side block with an Engineer's Hammer to form the multiblock. Input from the top, Steel is pulled from the front, and Slag is pulled from the back.

You can also attatch 2 Blast Furnace Preheaters to use RF to speed up the process of making Steel. RF is pushed in from the top, and the Blast Furnace Preheaters are attatched at the sides of the Improved Blast Furnace.
Punching trees! Getting wood! Excitement!

§lVanilla tools above stone (aside from hoes) are useless except for crafting recipes. You want to use Tinkers' Construct mostly. However, without a Smeltery, you can only use flint or other non-metallic tools. These are the blocks required to make Tinkers' tools. Don't spend too much making these, as they will be made obsolete by metal tools once those are made available. These quests REQUIRE the oak planks variant to be completed.

§rThe Stencil Table is what you use to turn regular Stencils into Patterns. Put the Stencils in the left slot, choose the pattern you need, and take it out of the right slot. There are about 25 stencils required to make all the patterns, not counting the ones it takes to make the blocks.

Put the patterns into the Pattern Chest, and make sure it is placed touching the Part Builder directly, which will let the Part Builder access all the Patterns it needs. Put the pattern in the far left slot, then put the material you want to make the part out of in the slot directly to the right of the one with the pattern in it. Metallic parts cannot be created without a Smeltery, so stick to something like Flint. You can also use Certus Quartz, Sapphire, Peridot, or Ruby if you have the materials. Cactus, Bone, Slimes Crystals of all colors, Paper, Obsidian, and Thaumium also are non-metallic, and give unique or useful modifiers that don take up a modifier slot.

The Tool Station is where it all comes together. Choose the tool you wish to create on the right of the GUI. Place the tool parts you require in the appropriate slots. Name that sucker, and pull out the finished product! If you wish to apply modifiers to the tool, place the tool in the mid-right slot on the left side, and the modifiers in the other 2. The "Materials and You" book (or you know, the rest of the internet) should have a list of modifiers and their effects in it.

§lThe Ball of Moss is an invaluable modifier, even at late game. Tools with the modifier slowly automatically repair themselves. This saves a ton of resources because you won't have to repair the tool ever. Also, if you want to get the Sharpness upgrade, 3 Certus Quartz is an entire level as opposed to the giant amount of Nether Quartz it would usually take.

§rYou can use a Chisel to turn Stone Bricks into Mossy Stone Bricks and use those!

§lA Smeltery is an essential tool for the young Tinkerer. If you don't want to crawl along the bottom of rivers and swamps for clay and sand, you can often find smeltery parts in Villages. The Smeltery is fueled by Lava in the Seared Tank, and also doubles ore output. A good tool to make Pickaxe Heads out of is Bronze, an alloy of Copper and Tin at a 3:1 ratio.

§rFor the average 3x3x1 interior Smeltery, you need a total of 104 Seared Bricks (the item). That amounts to 104 (64+40) Sand, Gravel, and Clay.

§lAs you may or may not have noticed, the recipe for Buckets has drastically changed. In the meanwhile, Lava can be moved to a Smeltery via the Can from Forestry! You can use it for other stuff too, I guess. They cannot place fluids in the world, however.

§rCans can hold 1000mB. In layman's terms, that's one bucket.

§lGears can currently only be created using the Gear Cast and the metal the Gear is made of.

§rThe Gear Cast is made using the Stone Gear and 2 Gold/Aluminum Brass in a Smeltery.

§lItty-bitty generation speed. The Survivalist Generator is incredibly slow, but fuel efficient. It's also probably the only thing you can make right now, so you've gotta deal with it for a while. To use Extra Utilities generators, you have to use IE Wire Coils or TE Fluxducts to transfer the RF; you can't just put the generator down next to the machine.

§rA single chunk of Coal in this bad boy will make you 80,000RF total, but at only 5RF/t. 20t in a second means that's 100RF/s. Not a whole lot, but it's workable for now. It's a good idea to use this to fill a Capacitor slowly instead of directly feeding machines, as it likely won't keep up with its RF demands.

§k§l§r§lThe Coke Oven is an important part of the modpack. The Coal Coke doesn't hurt either. It might be good to automate this fairly quickly, which can be done with just a hopper going in and one coming out, with some Cans or something similar to collect the Creosote.

§rThe Immersive Engineering Coke Oven is a multiblock. It is a 3x3x3 cube of Coke Bricks. Right click on any of the center blocks with an Engineer's Hammer to form the multiblock.

§lThese tools are rather inneficient but early-game methods of getting parts for machinery.

§rThe Forge Hammer turns Ingots into Plates of the same kind. Used by crafting with Ingots, it loses durability rather fast. You're going to make a couple I'm sure.

The Cutter turns Plates into Cable of the same kind. Like the Forge Hammer, it also loses durability on use.

§lThese machines create items that are used in many machine crafting recipes.

§rSupply the Thermionic Fabricator with RF, set the recipe by placing the required items in the required slots, and place the items into the bottom slot. Put Sand or Glass into the top right, and if it has a valid recipe, it will be turned into Molten Glass and be used in the recipe.

Lasers provide power to the Assembly Table and similar machines. Place the Laser down by the machine and connect the Laser to a source of RF. It will shoot a laser beam charged with RF to the machine. More lasers = more RF/t = faster assembly.

The Assembly Table makes Chipsets, among other items used in recipes. Place the items that the recipe requires in the left side, click on the result you want, and make sure there is a Laser with energy nearby. It takes a while for items to craft in it, so be patient. Items crafted will not be stored in the inventory, but be shot out into the world, or placed into an inventory that is touching it, like a chest.

§lPure Certus Quartz is super important for stuff right? What do you mean isn't this a little early for getting Pure Certus Quartz? Didn'tcha know? Certus Quartz Seeds now take SIXTEEN FULL REAL LIFE HOURS TO GROW.

§rMake as many as you're comfortable with right now, because you'll need them later. Throw them in water and just wait.

§lThere are some recipes that reqire metal dusts instead of ingots. These dusts can be created using the Quartz Grindstone. Place the Grindstone, place the Crank on it, and hold right click on the Crank to, well, crank it. You can put metals or ores in the top left, and the dusts are put into the bottom right slots. A single ore turns into 2 dusts, which are smelted into an ingot each, so this can be used for early-game ore doubling.

§l§r§rCranks will break if they are used when the Grindstone has nothing to grind.
§lThe first steps towards a civilized way of life.

§f§3§8§l§l§f§l§l§m§o§r§m§k§r§d§0§1§7§c§l§7§l§8§l§f§f§lRubber, made from a sticky goo. Obtained kinda like Maple Syrup.
§

§fRubber tree resin drops, when clicked with a Tree Tap drops Sticky Resin, which is smelted into Rubber

§lHow many Forge Hammers have you made so far? Check your Statistics! $20 on it being more than 5. The Metal Former uses EU to turn Ingots into Plates, Cables, and many other things that usually would take and break a Forge Hammer and a Cutter.

§r§rThe Metal Former uses EU, not RF, so you can't just connect this to your Fluxducts or Energy Conduits or however you've decided to move RF around. You need to use Cables, preferably insulated. You can convert RF into EU and back using Energy Converters.

§lThe Steam Dynamo is a great early-game way to generate RF. It uses furnace fuel, such as coal, to heat up water that can be piped in and turn it into Steam. The Steam is then converted into RF if it can leave the engine.

§rThe Steam Dynamo will begin to create steam as soon as it is supplied with fuel and water.

§lA rather slow, but easy to set up method to get Steel is the Immersive Engineering Blast Furnace. A single Steel Ingot takes 60 seconds to bake. You need to use Coal Coke as fuel, you can't use anything else.

§rThere are 3 recipes to make the Blast Bricks: Glue, which requires you to stick a Horse into a Smeltery; Ender Pearls; and TNT. Make a 3x3x3 and click the center with an Engineer's Hammer.

§lThe Arcane Worktable is one of the ways Thaumcraft adds for crafting things. Some recipes need Primal Vis Crystals. See your Basic Information tab of the Thaumonomicon for details.

§rRight click a crafting table with Salis Mundus to get the Arcane Workbench.

The Research Table is how you learn how to make most Thaumcraft blocks and items. You have to unlock Research Notes in the Thaumonomicon using aspect points you get by scanning blocks and items using the Thaumometer. You have to scan things in a certain order. To make the Research table, place to Tables next to eachother and right-click with Scribing Tools. These will be used up as you do the research minigame (see the Thaumonomicon for details), and refill it with Ink Sacs to continue using them.
§lThe Iron Chests mod adds new chests made of different metals with more inventory space.

§lThe Witches' Oven is how you get special Bewitchment Ingredients. Put Empty Jars in, some furnace fuel, and then saplings. Different saplings give different ingredients, as shown by JEI.

§r

§lThe Electric Furnace uses EU to smelt items, similar to the Furnace. It's probably the first energy-powered furnace that will be available to you.

§rThe Induction Furnace is an upgraded version of the Electric Furnace. It has an interesting mechanic where the longer it's running, the faster it smelts. At max speed, it's much faster than the Electric Furnace. To keep it running, and therefore hot, while no items are inside of it, you can give it a redstone signal. However, it uses EU so long as it runs, even if empty. If you want to keep it running without having a lever on it, you can put a Redstone Signal Inverter Upgrade in it, which will make it think it has a signal when it doesnt, and vice-versa.

§lThe Drawer Controller allows you to access every single connected Storage Drawer from sources like the Inventory Panel, ME Storage Bus, or just right clicking the controller with a hand to fill connected drawers.

§rThe Drawer Controller doesn't have to be directly touching every Drawer, it just has to be touching one that is touching another that is touching another etc. So if you have a wall of Drawers, so long as the Controller is touching one of them, you can access them all from it.

§lThe Extractor uses EU to extract extra rubber from Sticky Resin and Rubber Wood.

§rIn addition to giving more Rubber, the Extractor can turn Clay/Brick/Snow blocks into 4 of their item, remove the dye from Wool, and several other things.
§lThe Compressor is a special machine that creates items needed in crafting recipes.

§lThe Mining Laser is a mining tool, that shoots lasers. Pretty straight forward. The Mining Laser has many modes: Mining, with normal beam and average power usage; Low-focus, with a very short beam range and low energy usage; Long-range, with a stronger beam that can penetrate more blocks and a higher energy usage; Scatter, shoots 25 beams in front of you, shotgun style, with an average power usage multiplied per beam; Explosive, beam explodes upon hitting a block, higher power usage; Horizontal, same as mining mode except the beam can only move horizontally; and Super-heat, where blocks drop what they regularly smelt into if possible (ie, if you shoot Iron Ore, it will drop an Iron Ingot). To change the mode, go into your conrols and find IC2 Mode Switch Key, and hold that and right click with the Mining Laser in your hand.

§r

§lThe Magma Crucible and Fluid Transposer work together to make new materials. The Magma Crucible melts items into fluids and then the Magma Crucible applies those fluids to other items.

§rPlace the item you wish to melt into the Magma Crucible and feed it RF to melt it. Any tier of Magma Crucible will work with the quest.

The Fluid Transposer takes mixes fluids and items to make new things. Fluids can be pipes in through the blue side of the machine, so you can put it next to the Magma Crucible and set it up that way. Items go into the blue sides as well, and then it uses RF to combine them.
The Induction Smelter works similarly to alloying, you put two things together to make a new one. The Induction Smelter is the only way to get Slag, along with several other things.

§lThe Diamond Drill works almost identically to the regular Mining Drill, except is faster and can mine Obsidian-level blocks.

§rAgain, the Diamond Drill must be charged to use. The Diamond Drill uses more EU per block than the Mining Drill does.

§lThe Mining Drill is a relatively early-game, well, mining drill. You mine with it. The Mining Drill does not use durability, it uses EU. Charge it in a BatBox or something else that charges.

§rThe Mining Drill can only mine whatever an Iron Pickaxe would be able to. You can right-click to place a torch if there is one anywhere in your inventory.

§lTurning Uranium Ore into Uranium Fuel Rods is a rather complicated process requiring a bunch of machines.

§rCrushed Uranium ore can be made in either a Macerator or Rock Crusher.

The Ore Washing Plant turns water and Crushed Uranium Ore into a Purified Crushed Uranium Ore, 2 Tiny Piles of Lead Dust, and a Stone Dust.

A full Hazmat suit protects the player from getting radiated by holding Uranium, which acts similar to the Wither effect, killing quickly.

§lThe Witches' Altar gains Altar Power by having more nature stuff around it. You can also place stuff on top like a Wither Skull or a Candelabra. Check the wiki to see what is best.

§rThe Altar is a 3x2x1 multiblock, totalling 6 blocks.

§lThe Blood Altar is probably the most important part of Blood Magic. This will eventually be a giant multiblock. At the largest tier, tier 6, it takes up a 23x23x9 space.

§rI recommend checking the wiki and building the altar out of cobblestone, replacing it with what it actually needs as you get the blocks.

§lThe final altar on the list, the Infusion Altar from Thaumcraft. 

§rSee Infusion in the Artifice tab in your Thaumonomicon for more information on the Infusion Altar.

§lThe Witches' Cauldron is used to craft similar to Thaumcraft's Crucible. Set a fire underneath it (preferably using Netherrack), give it some water, and throw in the ingredients. Be extremely careful that you put in the correct ingredients, as they cannot be gotten back if you make a mistake, and some recipes are incredibly complicated. If the Cauldron starts emitting white swirls and making noises, the brew is ready to take out. Right click with an empty bottle to bottle it.

§rThe Witches' Cauldron can have water pumped into it automatically. You can get a chance of extras by wearing Witches' clothes.
The Distillery is yet another crafting mechanic from Witchery. It uses Altar Power to function, so it must be placed near an Altar with sufficient Altar Power.

§r§lThe Portal to Alfheim is a multiblock. It requires a pretty steady stream of Mana. The crafting recipe requires a tier 4 Blood Altar minimum.

§rRight click on the Elven Gateway Core to activate the Portal. Throw in certain items in to get other certain items out. See JEI or the Lexica Botania for details.
The Guardian of Gaia fight gives pretty good drops, which are used in certain crafting recipes. To make the Gaia Pylons, you need at least a Tier 5 Blood Altar.

§lThe Creative Portable Tank allows you to have an infinite amount of any single fluid. One of the three craftable creative items in this modpack.

§rNeeds to be crafted in the Dire Crafting Table.

0:10.command:8: say @s obtained the Creative Portable Tank. Unlimited Liquid Possibilities!

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lThe BC Quarry uses MJ to mine an area down to Bedrock. By default, it has an area of 9x9x4, which can be changed using Land Marks. Once it has RF, it starts to clear the area required and build the frame. Once that happens, it starts mining and putting the blocks into the inventory or pipe above it. If none is available, it is spit out at extreme velocity and gets all over the floor, and generally takes a while to mop up.

§rThe Quarry is not upgradable. A Redstone signal will turn it off. The more MJ you give it, the faster it goes. The Quarry gets a bit confused with Lava, so try to Pump that out sharpish.

§n§nTo convert RF/EU to MJ use Energy Converters!

§lThe Excavator "mines" ores that are in Mineral Deposits. Mineral Deposits cannot be found in any way except for using a Core Sample Drill. Place the Core Sample Drill anywhere in the world, and power it. Mineral Deposits are per chunk, and as such you might have to explore quite a bit before you find a chunk with a Mineral Deposit.

§rHit F3+G to see chunk borders. If the chunk you are in doesn't have an Ore Deposit, go one chunk over and repeat. An entire Ore Deposit has roughly a Diamond Chest or more's worth of ores.

See the Heavy Machinery tab of your Engineer's Manual to find out how to make the multblock.

§lThe Mob Crusher instantly kills regular mobs like Creepers, Skeletons, Zombies, and Wither Skeletons. It uses RF to run, and each mob kill produces some Mob Essence.

§rIf you put a pipe or inventory on the back of the Mob Crusher, then the items are put in there. The Mob Crusher has a range of 1x3x1, which can be expanded with Range Addons.

§lThe Killer Joe is a special machine that uses any sword that you place inside of it to kill mobs in a 5x5x4 area in front of it. While you can't put Tinkers' Construct weapons in it, most other swords work. Enchantments applied to the sword also take effect, but the sword takes durability damage as if it was used like normal. Mobs are not instantly killed, but have to be attacked the same amount of times as usual using the sword inside of it. Beware, mobs will attack the Killer Joe if they survive the first attack, which means that Creepers will explode and Blazes will light things on fire. Use with caution.

§rThe Killer Joe does not use RF or EU, but instead requires Nutrient Distillation be pumped into it. 1400mB is required to function, but it can store up to 2000mB. Experience gets sucked into it, which can be pumped out or put into your own XP, while items are left on the ground to be collected with a Vacuum Hopper or similar methods.

§lThe Mob Duplicator uses RF and Mob Essence to spawn the mob inside of the Mob Imprisonment Tool.

§rRight-click a mob with the Mob Imprisonment Tool to capture the mob and put it in the tool.

The Exact Copy mode uses more RF and Mob Essence, but spawns an exact copy of the mob you caught. This means if you caught something with low health, the mobs spawned will have low health. If you caught a Wither Skeleton, Wither Skeletons will be spawned in the Overworld.

§lThe Powered Spawner is, well, an RF-powered spawner. To set the mob, you have to combine it with a Broken Spawner (which is gotten by mining a Spawner) in an Anvil, which takes about 30 levels.

§rYou can mine a vanilla Spawner to get a Broken Spawner. If you want to get a different mob's Spawner, you can combine it with a filled Soul Vial in an Anvil to set the Broken Spawner to the mob inside of the Vial.

Combine the Broken Spawner and Powered Spawner in the Anvil to set the Powered Spawner to that mob. It runs on RF only, and can be upgraded with Double-Layer or Octadic Capacitors, which makes it faster and has more RF capacity.

§lThe Laser Drill doesn't actually mine, per se. Instead, it essentially turns RF into ores. There are some slots that you can put colored Laser Focii to increase the chance of getting certain ores. Hit U on the Focii to see which ores they increase the chance of getting.

§rThe RF does not go directly into the Laser Base. Instead it goes into the Laser Drill, which shoot into the Laser Base. Place up to 4 around the Laser Base with 1 empty block between so that the side with the hole is facing the Laser Base. Don't get into the beam, it stings!

Place the Laser Base 1 block below the build limit, so you can place a chest on it to collect the materials. The higher you place it, the less RF it requires. The Laser Base must have either Void or Bedrock underneath it, nothing else. That means you must dig directly below it until it hits Bedrock, or place it somewhere that has access to the Void.

§lThe Charged Porter allows you to teleport to the bound Matter Receiver using RF in the Charged Porter.

§rShift right click a Matter Receiver to bind the Charged Porter to it. You can only set one teleport location using it. Right click to teleport to it if it has RF.
§lWith the RFTools Dimension Manual you can accomplish anything! It houses all information known to man about creating your own custom dimensions.

§lThe Mining Dimension is supposed to preserve the Overworld by providing a new dimension to put your quarries in. 

§rThe Mining MultiTool acts as both a crafting component for the portal and the activator. Craft 6 Portal Frame blocks (that's the absolute minimum, 4 for the sides and 2 for the top and bottom. They can be any size, but this is the least you can do it with) and then build it in the world like you would a Nether Portal. Then, use the Mining MultiTool as you would use a Flint and Steel with the Nether Portal to activate it. To go through the portal, you have to sneak through it.

The Twilight Forest is a dimension filled with dungeons and magic. There is a strict progression you must go through if you want to explore everything this dimension has to offer. Beware, however. The Twilight Forest is fairly server intensive. If you are stuck, you can check the Twilight Forest's achievements page in the pause menu for detailed instructions.

§lSuper Factory Manager is a 1.12 Port of Steve's Factory Manager. SFM allows for extremely precise and complex automation that pipes can't do. You can pull and push from specific slots of an inventory, interact with Redstone, change Signs, break and place blocks, and so much more with SFM.

§rThe Machine Inventory Manager is the key to SFM. The Machine Inventory Manager alone can only interact with inventories it is directly touching, but with Inventory Cables you can extend it's reach. To explain how it works, let's automate Inscribers with it. Place the Inscriber and an inventory, like a chest, containing the parts required to make the circuits either touching the Machine Inventory Manager or an Inventory Cable leading to it, and then open the Machine Inventory Manager. All commands start with a Trigger, so make one and place it in the work area. Make an input command and attatch it to the Trigger. Set the inventory to the chest and set a whitelist for, for example, gold ingots. Make an output, connect it to the input, set it to the Inscriber, and set it to target the North, South, East, or West sides. Any of these, assuming that the Inscriber hasn't been rotated to be on it's side, will work to push items into or pull items out of the Inscriber. Create another input hooked to the last output and set it to target the N/S/E/W side of the Inscriber and whitelist Printed Logic Circuits, then connect another output on the chest, or barrels or wherever you want to output it. Using SFM, you can fully automate all the circuits by having one Inscriber per printed circuit type and another final one that combines them. For reference, the top side of the Inscriber puts items into the top slot, the bottom into the bottom slot, and the sides interact with the middle and output slots.

§lThe Metal Press is a multiblock that turns ingots plates, gears, or rods, depending on what mold it's using. Right click on the multiblock while holding the mold to insert it. Feed RF through the top.

§rSee the Engineer's Manual to see a visual guide to how to build it.

§lRedstone Arsenal adds RF-powered tools and armor based around Thermal Expansion. 

§rFlux-Infused Armor uses RF instead of durability. When filled with RF, the armor negates almost 100% of the damage taken. It also has a very high enchantability.

§lThe Flux-Infused JetPlate is the final tier of the Thermal Expansion path with Simply Jetpacks. It has the same armor rating as the regular Flux-Infused Chestplate, and works as a very fast jetpack.

§rThe Flux-Infused JetPlace can store 50M RF.
§lThe second-to-last tier of TE jetpack is the Resonant Jetpack. It's even faster, stores 25 000 000 RF, and uses 450 RF/t while flying.
§lThis Armored Capacitor Pack not only gives you the ability to carry power but also protect you from losing it.

§lStoring energy is just as important as creating it. The Immersive Engineering Capacitors are a great way to store energy early to mid game.

§rYou can easily convert RF to EU using Energy Converters. So you can use it for both!
§lThe Certus Quartz Wrench is a useful tool for Applied Energistics. When used in recipes, you get the Certus Quartz Wrench back, so don't be afraid to use it.

§lIn 1.7.10 you could convert RF to EU per Immersive Engineering Wires, in newer Minecraft versions IE dropped this support. Thats why we added the Mod Energy Converters.

§l§e§fLike in 1.7.10. 1 EU is 4 RF. On a side note, you can also convert to MJ (Buildcraft)!

§lThe Creative Energy Cell produces infinite RF up to 25 000 RF/t per side.

§l§rNeeds to be crafted in the Dire Crafting Table.

0:10.command:8: say @s obtained the Creative Power Cell. His Power Level is OVER 9000

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lEnder IO's Dark Armor has many upgrades to make the armor better and more powerful. The upgrades are applied in an Anvil, by putting the armor piece together with certain items using XP. Hold shift while hovering over them in your inventory to see what upgrades you can apply, and what they do.

§rWithout upgrades, Dark Armor takes full durability damage without any RF storage. The more Empowered upgrades applied, the more RF it stores and the less durability damage it takes. However, even when fully upgraded, it does take some durability damage, so you will have to eventually repair it with more Dark Steel.

§lThe Dark Soularium JetPlate is the final tier of the Ender IO path of Simply Jetpacks. While it doesn't use one, it has the same armor rating as a Dark Plate, and works as a very fast jetpack.

§rThe Dark Soularium JetPlate can store 60M RF.

§lThe second highest tier of Ender IO jetpack is the Vibrant Jetpack. It can store 20 000 000 RF and uses 450 RF/t to fly.

§r
§lThis Armored Capacitor Pack not only gives you the ability to carry power but also protect you from losing it.

§lJetpacks are extremely useful in that you can use them to fly, which is much faster than climbing ladders, not to mention you can do it anywhere. This tier isn't very fast, and only stores 800 000 RF and uses 32 RF/t while flying, but it's better than nothing!

§rSimply Jetpacks has 2 paths you can use for jetpacks: Thermal Expansion and Ender IO. These quests are for Thermal Expansion.

§lThe next highest tier for TE jetpacks is the Vibrant Jetpack. It is very fast, stores 6 000 000 RF, and uses 200 RF/t while in use.

§r

§lThe next tier of TE jetpacks is the Hardened Jetpack. It's faster, and stores 3 000 000 RF, and uses 50 RF/t when flying.

§rYou can craft armor plating to put on jetpacks! And you can remove it just as easy!

§lThe final tier of Flux Pack is the Resonant Flux Pack. It can store 40 000 000 RF, and can input/output at 20 000 RF/t.

§rNaturally, the higher tiers can have better armor applied to them.

§lThe second tier of Flux Pack stores 12 000 000 RF, and can send/recieve 6000 RF/t.

§rFrom this tier onwards, you can apply armor to your Flux Packs. You can also take them off just as easy, and you get to keep the armor plating!

§lFlux Packs are worn as chestplates and will charge all your armor and held items (that CAN be charged) with RF. There are several tiers, but this is the first.

§rThe Leadstone Flux Pack holds 1 500 000 RF, and can send/receive 800 RF/t.

§r§lThe Conductive Jetpack is the first tier of Ender IO jetpacks. It can store 80 000 RF and uses 32 RF/t to fly.

§rYou can put armor on the jetpacks, to make them protect you as well as give utility.

§lThe next tier of Ender IO jetpacks is the Electrical Steel Jetpack. It can store 400 000 RF and uses 50 RF/t to fly.

§rEach tier of jetpack is faster than the last.
The next tier of Ender IO jetpack is the Energetic Jetpack. It can store 4 000 000 RF and uses 200 RF/t to fly.

§lThe final tier of Capacitor Pack is the Quadruple-Layer Capacitor Pack. It stores 20 000 000 RF and can I/O at 20 000 RF/t.

§rNaturally, higher tiers can have better armor attached.

§lThe next tier of Capacitor Pack is the Double-Layer Capacitor Pack. It can hold 4 000 000 RF and can I/O at 4000 RF/t.

§rFrom this tier on, the Capacitor Packs can have armor applied to them.

§r§lSimply Jetpacks also adds Capacitor Packs, which are worn as chestplates and charge your held items and armor.

§rThe Basic Capacitor Pack hold 800 000 RF and can I/O at 800 RF/t.

§lUU-Matter is very useful. It allows you to turn EU into almost any item.

§rThe Mass Fabricator uses 1 000 000 EU to make 1mB of UUM. When supplied with Scrap from a Recycler, it is much faster and efficient, needing only 166 666 EU and 34 Scrap per mB of UUM.

The Scanner breaks down an item or block and puts it's pattern into a Pattern Storage block touching it.

The Replicator should touch the Pattern Storage. Click the arrows at the top of the GUI to choose which pattern to create using UU-Matter. Different items require different amounts of UU-Matter.

§lThe Nuclear Reactor is very... explodey. One of the best blocks to protect your base from meeting it's untimely demise is Reinforced Stone. A double layer of Reinforced Stone is best for completely neutralizing a Nuclear Reactor's explosion.

§rCF Powder plus a bucket of water in a Fluid Canning Machine in Fluid Enriching mode makes a bucket of Construction Foam. A single CF Powder is good for 10 blocks of Reinforced Stone.

To fill the CF Sprayer, place it into the top left slot of the Canning Machine while Construction Foam is in it.

Place down the Iron Scaffolds in the configuration you want your Reinforced Stone to be in. Right click the blocks with the CF Sprayer, and wait for it to dry. You can also right click it with sand to instantly harden it.

§r§lScrap significantly speeds up the Mass Fabricator. Scrap Boxes do even more.

§rPut anything into the Recycler, give it EU, and it has a 1 in 8 (12.5%) chance of turning into Scrap.

§lAn IC2 Nuclear Reactor is one of the best ways to get EU large-scale. This is a very complicated machine and very hard to explain through text, so visit the wiki page for this at tinyurl.com/IC2Reactor. You can look online for the best reactor designs. Beware: Nuclear Reactors can explode if they get too hot!

§r§rThe Nuclear Reactor will not run unless it has a redstone signal. You can place up to 6 Reactor Chamber blocks touching the sides of the Nuclear Reactor to maximize the size of the Nuclear Reactor.

§lFuel Rods (Uranium Depleted) are the product of entirely using a Fuel Rod (Uranium). If you put it into a Thermal Centrifuge, you get a Tiny Pile of Plutonium, 4 Uranium 238, and Iron Dust. The Plutonium is what you want, it is very useful.

§r§rOnce a Nuclear Reactor has been running for long enough, the Fuel Rods will become Depleted. Depleted Fuel Rods do not generate EU in the Reactor, and only serve to be put back into the Thermal Centrifuge.

I personally recommend using the Replicator to get 9 Tiny Piles of Plutonium for now. Much quicker than waiting for 9 Fuel Rods (Uranium) to deplete. You get 1 Tiny Pile per Fuel Rod (Uranium Depleted), which takes 2.75 real life hours.

§lThe Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator is fueled by Pellets of RTG Fuel and makes EU. Pellets of RTG Fuel are fairly expensive to make, but they are not depleted or used up while making EU in this. However, at max speed with 6 Pellets of RTG Fuel inside of it, it generates only 32EU/t.

§rWhat a mouthful.

§lPellets of RTG Fuel are used in several recipes. 

§rIt is also used to make infinite energy in the Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator.

§lMOX Nuclear Fuel is a hybrid of Plutonium and Uraniun 238. The Fuel Rod (MOX) only lasts half as long as the Fuel Rod (Uranium), but gives much more EU. MOX becomes more efficient as the heat rises.

§rDepleted MOX Fuel Rods give more Plutonium than Uranium Fuel Rods do.

§lIridium is probably the hardest item to get at this part of the game. It needs 80M RF, plus 1 Pellet of RTG Fuel and a MOX Nuclear Fuel. You definitely want to use tons of Lasers for this, rather than just having 6. Once you have one, I recommend using the Replicator to get more instead of making it out of the MOX and RTG.

§rMaking Iridium with the Replicator takes about 20 000 000 EU per. Making it regularly requires 59 Tiny Piles of Plutonium, which takes roughly three forevers.

§lNow that you have Pellets of RTG Fuel available, you can make Big Reactors. Big Reactors are much easier to set up and run, with no chance of exploding.

§rThe smallest Big Reactor possible makes ~258 RF/t, and it uses 0.215 mB/t. It gets hot quickly, which makes it less fuel efficient, so you're going to want to eventually make a larger, cooler reactor.

§lAn ME System does not use RF or EU, but AE. You can convert RF and EU into AE by connecting it into the Enegy Acceptor and piping it out with Fluix Cables. You can also supply power through the ME Controller, but then that is one less side you can pull channels from.

§r1 EU = 2 AE. 1 AE = 2 RF.

§lThe Iridium Drill is the highest-tier drill in IC2. It is faster than the Diamond Drill, but uses more EU.

§rWhile holding the Mode Switch Key (see the controls options), you can right click with the Iridium Drill to toggle between Silk Touch and Fortune III on the drill.

§lThe ME Controller gives you more channels to work with. Each side adds 8 or 32 channels. It can also accept energy and convert it to AE. It is a multiblock, and you can only have one per ME System. 

§r§rThe ME Controller also accepts RF and EU to power the ME system, but that is one less side you can use channels with.

§lThe Portal Gun allows you to use your two mouse buttons to shoot two linked portals. Enter one, exit the other. 
§r
The regular Portal Gun is not specific to the player. If two people use the default Portal Gun, they would overwrite eachother's portals.
Gingers are a crossbreed between Mustard Seeds and Peanuts

betterquesting:10.name:8: Made Out of Buttons and Wires
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lAE2 machines are hooked up and powered via Fluix conduits. Channels are a very special mechanic: most Busses or AE2 Machines take up a channel. Different cables have different amounts of channels available.

§rME Glass Cables can only carry 8 channels. You can connect Busses to them.

ME Smart Cables can also only hold 8 Channels at once, but you see a visual representation of them. You can hook up Busses with them also.

ME Dense Cables can carry 32 channels, and you can see a visual representation of them. However, you cannot connect Busses to them.

§lThese Conduits can fit in the same block as other Ender IO Conduits. They cannot connect to Busses or Panels.

§rME Conduits carry 8 channels.

Dense ME Conduits carry 32 channels.
Cranberries are a crossbreed between Blueberries and Grapes.

§lStorage Cells are placed into the ME Drive. Every Storage Cell can only take 63 unique items, but the different tiers can hold certain amounts of bytes. 8 items take up 1 byte, no matter the size of a regular stack. Going straight for the max size Storage Cell isn't necessarily the best idea, because then you still only have 63 possible unique items, even if it's a lot more of those 63 items.§l

§rI won't ask you to make any specific Storage Cell, as depending on where you are you can afford larger ones.
§lCactus Fruit are a crossbreed between Onion and Ginger.

§lThe ME Crafting Terminal allows you to access items stored in your ME Storage Cells, and has an in-built crafting table.

§rThe ME Crafting Terminal connects to an ME Cable and it takes up 1 channel.

§lNo, not that kind of bus. These Busses are essentially ways to interact with things outside of the ME System. These all take a channel each.

§rThe Import Bus pulls items from an inventory in front of it into the ME System it is connected to. For example, if you want to move all your items out of chests into your ME System, you would use a Dolly to move all your chests so that they're connected to an Import Bus, which will suck out all the items and put them into the System. You can set a whitelist on what to import by opening it and putting items into it. By default, the whitelist can only have 1. With 2 Capacity Cards, it can have 9.

The Export Bus pushes items out of the ME System into the inventory it is facing. You have to open the Bus and put the items you want to push out into it. Without Capacity Cards, you only can export 1 item. With 2 Capacity Cards, you can export 9.

The Storage Bus allows you to access inventories that are not a part of the ME system. If you place it facing, for instance, a Drawer Controller, you won't have to get rid of your entire wall of Drawers; instead, you'll be able to access them all from ME Terminals. This way, you won't waste precious Storage Cell space.

§lAE2's probably best feature is Autocrafting. This allows you to automatically craft whatever you define, which saves a surprising amount of time.

§r§rThe Crafting CPU is a multiblock. It must be a cuboid, meaning it has 6 sides maximum. It is made up of Crafting Co-Processing Units and Crafting Storages. The more Crafting CPUs, the faster it can craft things (so long as they don't require outside machines, which can only be sped up with their own mechanics). The more Crafting Storage you have, the more complicated of a recipe you can make. Having multiple Multiblocks allows you to autocraft multiple things at once.
The ME Pattern Terminal allows you to set recipes that can be autocrafted, either through regular crafting or through machines. You need Blank Patterns to begin with. For crafting table recipes, input the recipe to the crafting table gui to the left and hit the Encode Pattern Button and pull out the Encoded Pattern. For processing patterns, for instance Alloy Smelter or other things like that, click the Crafting Table to the right to switch modes. Then, put the inputs to the left and outputs to the right. Keep clicking to put more of the same item in if you need multiple or recieve multiple of one of the items.

The ME Interface is where you connect your ME System to processing or crafting. For processing, put the ME Interface (preferably the panel version, as you can put multiple in one block, and you specify which side of the cable) next to a machine, like an Alloy Smelter. Then, put a processing recipe into the bottom slots of the ME Interface. Connect an Import Bus to the machine to pull the finished item back into the ME System. Bingo presto! Automatic processing! For regular crafting, see the next task. ME Interfaces take up a channel each.

§lThe ME Wireless Access Point and Wireless Terminal allow you to wirelessly access your ME System's items.

§rThe ME Wireless Access Point is the central location that you have to be nearby to in order to use the Wireless Terminal. You can extend the range with Wireless Boosters at the cost of more AE/t usage.

The ME Security Terminal is how you bind your Wireless Terminal to the ME System. Place the Wireless Terminal in the top right and it will bind to that system.

The Wireless Terminal is essentially an ME Access Terminal that you can hold.

§lThe Arcane Crafting Terminal works as a regular Crafting Terminal AND an Arcane Worktable. You put your Wand in there, and craft like normal, but you have access to your entire ME System while doing it.

§r§r

§lThe ME Fluid Terminal allows you to access fluids in your ME System. You need to have Fluid Storage in your ME System to store fluids in it.

§rPut the thing you want to put the fluid into (bucket/can/whatever) into the left slot, and click what you want to put into it. Or, you can put a filled fluid container into the left slot, and it will go into the system.

§lThe Wireless Universal Terminal has different modes depending on what you craft together. To switch modes, shift right click it.

§rTo add a mode, craft a Wireless Terminal with an Access Terminal that you want to add support for. To make the max upgraded one, craft the regular Wireless Access Terminal with either a Fluid Terminal or Essentia Terminal, and then craft that with the other one.

To get a Wireless §lCrafting§r Terminal, craft a Wireless Terminal with a Crafting Terminal and a Fluix Pearl.
§lThe Essentia Terminal allows you to access Essentia in your ME System. To store Essentia in your ME System, you need Essentia Storage Cells.
§lThese Busses work exactly the same as the regular ones, but with Fluids.

§lThese Busses work exactly the same as the regular ones, but with Essentia.

§o§r§r
§lPrineapples are a crossbreed between Canteloupe and Bamboo Shoots.
§lBarley are a crossbreed between Barley and Soybean.

§lThe Infusion Provider allows the Infusion Altar to use Essentia from your ME System.

§rThe Infusion Provider has to be close to the Infusion Altar to work.
Onions are a crossbreed between Brussel Sprout and Celery.

§lRFTools dimensions are extremely RF intensive. Don't forget to bring a Porter!

§rWithout Dimlets, Dimensions are entirely random as far as traits go. Twilight Forest biome with multicolored Hardened Clay? Anything can happen. The Dimension Enscriber doesn't require RF, just an Empty Dimension Tab. Put that in, and if you have any Dimlets you want, stick those in too. Click "Store" to make the dimension.

Put the Realized Dimension Tab into the Dimension Builder. Dimensions require a ton of RF to build for the first time, and then continued RF to keep it on. The more complicated or intense the Dimension, the more RF it takes.

§lBrown Mushrooms are a crossbreed between Portatoes and Carrots.

§fFYI you will have to use Mycelium as the soil!
§lYou deserve it. This is one of the most complicated recipes in the modpack. This isn't it, however.
Chili Pepper are a crossbreed between Onion and Tomato.

betterquesting:10.name:8: This Is Going To Be Easy!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lThese Cores are the base ingredients for most recipes.

§rThe Draconic Core is probably the easiest thing you will ever craft in Draconic Evolution.

The Wyvern Core is 4 times the probable easiest thing you will make in Draconic Evolution, plus some other stuff.

§lRed Mushrooms are a crossbreed between Potatoes and Carrots.

§fFYI you will have to use Mycelium as the soil!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Need This and This and This...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lMana Dust is required to make certain things in Draconic Evolution. It's so confusing to make, I spelled it out for you here.

§r360mB of Primal Mana is required to make 1 Mana Dust. the smallest amount you can make at a time is 576mB. This takes 1 ingot of Mirion, 1 ingot of Pigiron, 2 ingots of Manasteel and 1000mB of OpenBlocks Liquid XP.
Especially that first ingredient can be tricky to make.

§lThe Pickaxe of the Wyvern is one of the best pickaxes in the game.  Check you Controls for "Tool and Armour Config GUI", and press that. Click the Pickaxe of the Wyvern, and you can modify the dig speed multiplier, area of effect, and whether or not it stops you from digging Tile Entities. The "Inv" tab allows you to place Enchanted Books into the item, which will enchant it. You can later remove these if you want.

§lThe Sword of the Wyvern is one of the most powerful ranged weapons in the game. Check you Controls for "Tool and Armour Config GUI", and press that. Click the Sword of the Wyvern, and you can change the AoE, similar to the Tinker's Construct's Scythe.

§rIn addition to the 20 attack damage (10 hearts), an additional 10% of the mob's health is removed. This means most mobs can be defeated in 10 hits or less, except for certain bosses that cap out damage like the Guardian of Gaia.


§r

betterquesting:10.name:8: I Swear There Was Dirt Here
betterquesting:10.desc:8: §lThe Shovel of the Wyvern is one of the best pickaxes in the game.  Check you Controls for "Tool and Armour Config GUI", and press that. Click the Shovel of the Wyvern, and you can modify the dig speed multiplier, area of effect, and whether or not it stops you from digging Tile Entities. The "Inv" tab allows you to place Enchanted Books into the item, which will enchant it. You can later remove these if you want.

§lThe Bow of the Wyvern is one of the most powerful ranged weapons in the game. Check you Controls for "Tool and Armour Config GUI", and press that. Click the Bow of the Wyvern, and you can modify several values. The more powerful you make the bow, the more RF it takes per shot. The "Inv" tab allows you to place Enchanted Books into the item, which will enchant it. You can later remove these if you want.

§lThe Dislocator allows you to teleport from anywhere in any dimension to a specific location for absolutely no cost. However, it can only have one location, and cannot be rebound. Shift right click to save the coords, dimension, and direction you are looking. Right click anywhere else to teleport there.

§rYou don't have to look at a block while binding it, otherwise you would be looking straight down when you teleport there. Just look straight ahead, or the direction you want to be looking when you teleport there.

§lWyvern armor some of the most powerful armor in Expert Mode. The Leggings and Boots of the Wyvern can be configured to let you run and jump faster and higher, and you can set it to only do so while sprinting.

§rWhile the Wyvern armor has RF, it produces shield. This shield works as essentially extra health, a buffer before your actual health is damaged.

§lDraconic armor is the most powerful armor in the modpack. It allows you to fly, see in the dark, see Nodes, jump high, run fast, and step up single blocks. Wearing charged Draconic armor, you are nearly invincible; you can even survive an IC2 Nuke point-blank.

§rPretty much the only thing that  has the ability to damage you at this stage is the Chaos Guardian. That, or someone messing with Bewitchment.

§lDimensional Shards only spawn in RFTools Dimensions. These Shards allow you to upgrade your machines. Hold Shift on a machine to see what Infusing the Shards into them will do.

§rPut the Shards in the slot to the left and the machine into the slot to the right. It may take more than a stack to fully infuse a machine.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Who Said the Wither Was Hard?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lThe Mob Grinder uses RF to kill mobs in front of it. It does not collect the items or XP, but it is capable of near instantly killing a Wither. It is also Wither-proof.

§rYou can also put furnace fuel into it instead of RF.

§lThis chest has 234 slots, can automatically smelt anything inside of it 5 items at a time, and you has a crafting table inside of it.

§rYou can also break the Draconium Chest and it will keep it's contents.

betterquesting:10.name:8: What's the Opposite of a Vacuum
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§lThe Energy Infuser quickly fills items with RF.

§r

§lAwakened Draconium is the next and final tier of crafting §lmaterials.
§r
Look into JEI, for the recipe
Mustard Seeds are a crossbreed between Chili Peppers and Beans.
§lThe Draconic Bow is the most powerful bow in the modpack. With this bow, you can machinegun fire arrows. You can configure how powerful the bow is in the GUI.
§lThe Draconic Pickaxe is the best pickaxe in the modpack. It works similar to the Pickaxe of the Wyvern, but has extra modifiers and has larger maximums.
§lThe Draconic Shovel is the best shovel in the modpack. It works similar to the Shovel of the Wyvern, but has extra modifiers and has larger maximums.
§lThe Draconic Sword is the second best pickaxe in the modpack. It works similar to the Sowrd of the Wyvern, but has extra modifiers and has larger maximums.

§lThe Draconic Staff of Power is the ultimate. It is a mixture of all of the other Draconic tools. It does the most damage, a whopping 60 damage (30 hearts), plus an additional 30% of the mob's health. It can be configured like the other tools.

§r

§lWhite Mushroom are a crossbreed between Red Mushrooms and Brown Mushrooms.

§fFYI you will have to use Mycelium as the soil!
Peanuts are a crossbreed between Beans and Bamboo Shoots.

§lThe Creative Flux Capacitor gives infinite RF. You deserve it, man.

§rNeeds to be crafted in the Dire Crafting Table.

0:10.command:8: say @s obtained the Creative Flux Capacitor. Doc Brown would be proud!

betterquesting:10.desc:8: Spice Leafs are a crossbreed between Tea and Chili Pepper
§lBellpeppers are a crossbreed between Chili Pepper and Spice Leaf
§lParnsips are a crossbreed between Carrot and Beet
Rutbagas are a crossbreed between Beet and Turnip.
§lSea Weeds are a crossbreed between Celery and Lettuce.

§lWheat is not a byproduct of breeding.

§rWheat grows on farmland.

§lPotatoes have to be in seed form to plant on Crop Sticks.

§rPotatoes grow on farmland.

§lCarrots have to be in seed form to plant on Crop Sticks.

§rCarrots grow on farmland.
§lSugar Cane is a crossbreed between Carrots and Wheat.
§lPumpkin is a crossbreed between Potatoes and Carrots
§lMelon is a crossbreed between Pumpkin and Carrots.
§lThe Dandelion is a crossbreed between Sugar Cane and Melons.
§lThe Poppy is a crossbreed between Sugar Cane and Pumpkins
§lBlue Orchids are a crossbreed between Poppies and Dandelions.§l
§lAllium is a crossbreed between Poppies and Blue Orchids.
§lThe Daisy is a crossbreed between Blue Orchids and Dandelion.§l
§lWhite Tulips are a crossbreed between Daisies and Dandelions.

§lMystical White Flowers are a crossbreed between Daisies and White Tulips.

§rMystical Flowers grow on Podzol.
§lOrange Tulips are a crossbreed between Daisies and Blue Orchids.

§lMystical Yellow Flowers are a crossbreed between Dandelions and Orange Tulips.

§rMystical Flowers grow on Podzol.

§lMystical Blue Flowers are a crossbreed between Allium and Blue Orchids.

§rMystical Flowers grow on Podzol.
§lRed Tulips are a crossbreed between Poppies and Allium.

§lMystical Red Flowers are a crossbreed between Red Tulips and Poppies.

§rMystical Flowers grow on Podzol.

§0§r§lAgricraft allows you to breed crops to make them better, or even create new crops!

§rPut seeds into the Seed Analyzer to get it's statistics. Seeds have 3 statistics: Growth, which is how fast the crop matures, Gain, which is how much you get from a single crop, and Strength, which is the resilience to weeds and ability to move with Clippers. Luckily, Infinity has weeds disabled, so you don't have to worry very much about Strength.


Crop Sticks are where you plant seeds to grow them the AgriCraft way. If you right-click a valid soil with them, it will the sticks down and allow you to plant crops there. Plants growing on these can be harvested by right-clicking instead of breaking. If you right-click Crop Sticks with Crop Sticks, you will put even more on, which allows you to crossbreed crops that are touching it. For instance, if you put 2 Crop Sticks onto soil between Carrots and Potatoes (assuming that they're on single Crop Sticks), there will be a chance that they will crossbreed into Pumpkins! They can also just spread the Carrots or Potatoes, so it's mildly chance-based.
